    <item>
      <title>MSMM Training: How To Get A Domain Name</title>
      <link>http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/index.php/get-your-domain-name/</link>
      <comments>http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/index.php/get-your-domain-name/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 05 Feb 2011 13:24:21 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>maxyself</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Main Street Marketing Machines]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[domain]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[how to]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Mike Koenigs]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[MSMM]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/?p=70</guid>
      <description>&lt;br/&gt;As you have read in my previous post I described how Main Street Marketing Machines teaches you to create a free report on the niche you have chosen using the tools within Traffic Geyser. The next thing Mike Koenigs shows you in great detail is how to publish a lead page on the internet. In order to achieve this there are several things you need to do. &lt;a href="http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/index.php/get-your-domain-name/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/main-street-marketing-machines-review-best-bonus-/Main_Street_Marketing_Machines_Review__BEST_Bonus_-MSMM_Training-_How_To_Get_A_Domain_Name.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<br/><div class="tweetmeme_button" style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;">
			<a href="http://api.tweetmeme.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2FMainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com%2Fblog%2Findex.php%2Fget-your-domain-name%2F"><br />
				<img src="http://api.tweetmeme.com/imagebutton.gif?url=http%3A%2F%2FMainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com%2Fblog%2Findex.php%2Fget-your-domain-name%2F&amp;style=normal&amp;b=2" height="61" width="50" title="MSMM Training: How To Get A Domain Name" alt="MSMM Training: How To Get A Domain Name" /><br />
			</a>
		</div>
<h1>MSMM Training: How To Get A Domain Name</h1>
<p><a href="http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tg7.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-124" title="MSMM Training: How To Get A Domain Name" src="http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tg7.png" alt="MSMM Training: How To Get A Domain Name" width="500" height="117" /></a>Almost every Internet Marketing specialist will advise you to spend time on how to get a domain name and chose wisely!!</p>
<p>As you have read in my previous post I described how <a href="http://www.mainstreetmarketingmachinesipadbonus.com/default.aspx?ref=bpmsmm">Main Street Marketing Machines</a> teaches you to create a free report on the niche you have chosen using the tools within <a href="http://www.TrafficGeyser.com/cmd.php?af=27873">Traffic Geyser</a>.  The next thing Mike Koenigs shows you in great detail is how to publish a lead page on the internet.  In order to achieve this there are several things you need to do.</p>
<p>First, try to find an available keyword loaded domain name and buy it.  There is a great number of registrars on the internet but Mike, and I incidentally, endorse <a href="http://www.godaddy.com">Godaddy.com</a>.  It has competitive pricing with great offers available all the time and extra services you might at some point need.  Since your lead page is targeted at the local market and a particular niche, the best domain would be a combination of location and business with a .com extension.  I’m saying that because even if some might say that a .com and .biz domain can rank the same in the search engines, the people that are going to be looking at the search results returned for their query trust the .com extension more than the .biz.  So in my opinion it would be better to have a less keyword loaded .com domain than a fully keyword loaded .biz domain.  Another point I would like to make since lots of people are asking this is about dashes in the URL, so far there doesn’t seem to be a penalization by the search engines on URLs but their algorithms change daily and you can’t know for sure that this will be the case tomorrow or next month. Hence f you can, grab the domain name without the dashes.</p>
<p>One thing you should know about <a href="http://www.godaddy.com">Godaddy.com</a> is that they have a, hmm how should I put this, a strong “up-sell” policy.  This means that they will try to sell you quite a lot of products along with the domain you are registering.  In case you are using Traffic Geyser you do not need any of these products since Mike and his team provide hosting for you.  Last time round Mike was saying that they were working on enhancing their services and sometime soon they are hoping to be able to register the domain name with them at a competitive price and not having to register it at godaddy.com.</p>
<p>One thing I would like to say about <a href="http://www.mainstreetmarketingmachinesipadbonus.com/default.aspx?ref=bpmsmm">Main Street Marketing Machines</a> is that it caters for both the experienced internet user and the complete newbie.  It takes everything one step at a time but also gives you advanced tips that even the most experienced might not know.<br />
If you do not want <a href="http://www.TrafficGeyser.com/cmd.php?af=27873">Traffic Geyser</a> to host your lead page you can set up your domain on your hosting, create the lead page as we will see in the next article and then upload it using FTP, which is embedded in <a href="http://www.TrafficGeyser.com/cmd.php?af=27873">Traffic Geyser</a>, to your hosting provider.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
