      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/?p=39</guid>
      <description>&lt;br/&gt;Main Street Marketing Machines (MSMM) is a course offered by Mike Koenigs that transforms you into a Main Street Marketing Expert. Mike shows you how to use all the available tools in Traffic Geyser, the platform they have designed and use, in order to become a Main street marketing expert. The first tool you get to use is the Opportunity Finder. &lt;a href="http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/index.php/how-to-find-your-niche/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/main-street-marketing-machines-review-best-bonus-/Main_Street_Marketing_Machines_Review__BEST_Bonus_-Main_Street_Marketing_Machines_MSMM__How_To_Find_Your_Niche.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<br/><div class="tweetmeme_button" style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;">
			<a href="http://api.tweetmeme.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2FMainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com%2Fblog%2Findex.php%2Fhow-to-find-your-niche%2F"><br />
				<img src="http://api.tweetmeme.com/imagebutton.gif?url=http%3A%2F%2FMainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com%2Fblog%2Findex.php%2Fhow-to-find-your-niche%2F&amp;style=normal&amp;b=2" height="61" width="50" title="Main Street Marketing Machines (MSMM)   How To Find Your Niche" alt="Main Street Marketing Machines (MSMM)   How To Find Your Niche" /><br />
			</a>
		</div>
<h1>Main Street Marketing Machines (MSMM) teaches you how to use all the available tools to find your niche</h1>
<p><a href="http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tg6.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-118 alignleft" title="Main Street Marketing Machines (MSMM)   How To Find Your Niche" src="http://MainStreetMarketingMachinesiPadBonus.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tg6-300x108.png" alt="Main Street Marketing Machines (MSMM)   How To Find Your Niche" width="300" height="108" /></a></p>
<p>How easy it is to find your niche? <a href="http://www.mainstreetmarketingmachinesipadbonus.com/default.aspx?ref=bpmsmm">Main Street Marketing Machines</a> <a href="http://www.mainstreetmarketingmachinesipadbonus.com/default.aspx?ref=bpmsmm">(MSMM)</a> is a course offered by Mike Koenigs that transforms you into a Main Street Marketing Expert.  Mike shows you how to use all the available tools in <a href="http://www.TrafficGeyser.com/cmd.php?af=27873">Traffic Geyser</a>, the platform they have designed and use, in order to become a Main street marketing expert.  The first tool you get to use is the Opportunity Finder.</p>
<p>It is a very helpful tool within <a href="http://www.TrafficGeyser.com/cmd.php?af=27873">Traffic Geyser</a> that will help you to choose the initial niche/business and location you will work in as well as every time you are looking to expand into new territory.</p>
<p>You could approach this tool from many different directions.</p>
<p>Perhaps you have already made up your mind that you would like to work at geographical locations near your place of residence or maybe you are knowledgeable in a particular niche and you know you can apply your experience using <a href="http://www.mainstreetmarketingmachinesipadbonus.com/default.aspx?ref=bpmsmm">MSMM</a> and don’t care about geographical location or you are open to all possibilities and are willing to go wherever the best opportunity is, in any case this tool will give you a measure of the “hunger” for your services in any particular niche and location.</p>
<p>As far as the use of the tool, it is pretty straightforward.  The first necessary step is for you to choose a location, you can always come back at this stage later in the process to change it if you want, and then choose Business type.  Based on these criteria you get a list with information on keywords, search results, Cost per click, paid ads and questions asked.</p>
<p>From this information you can see what the market for the niche and location you have chosen looks like.  You can hence choose keywords with low completion and increase your chances of rating high, look for low cost per click, if there are many local ads you might think it’s a bad thing but it is actually a good thing since it means that people in the location you have chosen are paying money to be promoted in that niche.</p>
<p>Having made your mind up you then move onto the last step of the process where the <a href="http://www.TrafficGeyser.com/cmd.php?af=27873">Opportunity Finder</a> gives you a list of rated prospects.  Can you believe that?  It’s a list of people or businesses that could become your customers if only you approach them with the results of your lead site.  Except for all the expected information such as name, address, telephone number and email address you get a rating for each prospect, the higher the rating the better has been the experience of customers having dealt with that prospect, it’s easy to understand that if the customers are satisfied you will probably be dealing with a good person or a well run company and hence you can more easily do business with them.</p>
<p>Having this information handy you are ready to go out and get them to pay you for all the leads you will produce for them.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
